.SH "NAME"
ibrdf \- read data bytes to file (board or device)
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
.ft B
.nf
#include <gpib/ib\&.h>
.fi
.ft
.HP \w'int\ ibrdf('u
.BI "int ibrdf(int\ " "ud" ", const\ char\ *" "file_path" ");"
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
ibrdf() is similar to
ibrd()
except that the data bytes read are stored in a file instead of an array in memory\&.
\fIfile_path\fR
specifies the save file\&. If the file already exists, the data will be appended onto the end of the file\&.
.SH "RETURN VALUE"
.PP
The value of
ibsta
is returned\&.
